  "phase_reasoning": "Two critical fixes required before CBT submission:\n\n1. WRONG COMMUNITY FUTURES OFFICE: The financial model names \"Community Futures Boundary in Grand Forks\" as the CBT Impact Investment Fund processing office. External verification confirms the correct office for Rossland is Community Futures South Kootenay (formerly Greater Trail) at 825 Spokane Street, Trail, BC. This is a factual error that would flag the application as having unverified local knowledge and could delay the review cycle.\n\n2. BREAK-EVEN INCONSISTENCY ACROSS DOCUMENTS: The financial model and CBT application brief show materially different break-even figures for the same scenarios (Realistic: Month 2 in financial model vs. Month 6-8 in CBT brief; Conservative: Month 15-17 vs. Month 22; Optimistic: Month 1 vs. Month 3-4). A CBT reviewer reading both documents will see the contradiction immediately. The financial model's figures are more defensible; the CBT brief needs to be updated to match.\n\nFour moderate fixes are also recommended but not blocking: update Rossland population from 4,100 to 4,300 (2021 Census confirmed); replace Mountain CoLab trajectory comparison (it is a volunteer co-op at half the price point, structurally incomparable); define the $75/month founding member promotional rate; update manager hours notes to match actual dollar amounts.\n\nAll prior Cycle 1 critical issues (KPI card discrepancies, GST footnote, Add-ons itemization, monthly ramp table, break-even definitions) have been successfully resolved. The document set is in strong shape \u2014 two targeted fixes away from CBT-ready.\"",
